- "Bring forth" means to retrieve or present;
- "Team's banner" refers to the team name;
- "Squad's emblem" refers to the squad name.

- 'Varsity' refers to the main or senior team in a school or organization;
- 'score' and 'race distance' are used to measure the performance of the team in races;
- 'participating in more than one race' ensures that the team's performance is consistent across multiple events.

sql:
SELECT AVG(
  CAST(SUBSTR(time, 1, INSTR(time, ':') - 1) AS REAL) * 60 +  -- Convert minutes to seconds
  CAST(SUBSTR(time, INSTR(time, ':') + 1) AS REAL)             -- Add the seconds
) AS average_time
FROM athlete_results;

